cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for detecting sarcasm in tweets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses neural models to extract author context, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also experiments with different datasets and achieves state-of-the-art performance, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the perception of sarcasm, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
